<title>UK: Derwent plans share issue.</title>
<headline>Derwent plans share issue.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-03-18</dateline>
<text>
<p>Property investment company Derwent Valley Holdings Plc said on Tuesday it would issue 2.87 million shares at 498p per share. The company said in a statement the proceeds will be used to finance its previously announced purchase of a property from MEPC for 14.3 million stg.</p>
<p>The new ordinary shares represent 7.36 percent of Derwent's issued share capital. SBS Warburg is broker and underwriter to the placing.</p>
<p>Derwent also announced that pre-tax profit for 1996 rose to 7.5 million stg from 4.4 million previously. It will pay a final dividend of 4.2p per share making a total of 6.1p for the year, up 10.9 percent.</p>
<p>--London Newsroom +44 171 542 4019</p>
